{
  "texts": [
    "Lastly, graphical models have been explored for their ability to represent and analyze the relationships and structures within data, such as social networks, to identify spam campaigns [15], [30], [31].",
    "B. AI and Machine Learning Models in Spam DetectionThe integration of AI and machine learning models into spam detection has significantly advanced the field, offering dynamic solutions capable of adapting to evolving spam tactics, including culturally relevant spam contexts [15], [32], [33], [34].",
    "Studies have detailed the application of pre-trained language models, like BERT and GPT, to understand and classify text-based communications with high accuracy [15], [35], [36].",
    "Transfer learning has been particularly noted for its efficiency, allowing models trained on large datasets to be fine-tuned for specific spam detection tasks [13], [18], [37], [38].",
    "Research into unsupervised learning models has revealed their potential in identifying spam without requiring labeled datasets, a significant advantage in rapidly changing spam landscapes [39], [40], [41]."
  ]
}